<doc id="889789" wikidata="Q7522927" url="?curid=889789" title="Singapore Chess Federation">
<text>The Singapore Chess Federation (Abbreviation: SCF) is the principal authority over all chess events in Singapore. SCF was founded in 1949 by Lim Kok Ann. The Federation is affiliated to the world governing body, International Chess Federation (FIDE), and is part of the ASEAN Chess Confederation and the Asian Chess Federation.

Its promotion of the game has caused participation in its youth and interschool events, among others, to jump from 517 in 1999 to over 1200 in 2004. As a result, Singapore has one of the highest number of chess players in schools per capita in Asia. 

The current president is International Master Hsu Li Yang. The current vice president is Grandmaster Wong Meng Kong.

==See also==
*Singaporean Chess Championship

