=== Other properties ===

* Any circulant is a matrix polynomial (namely, the associated polynomial) in the cyclic permutation matrix formula_31: formula_32 where formula_31 is given by the companion matrix formula_34
* The set of formula_2 circulant matrices forms an formula_22-dimensional vector space with respect to addition and scalar multiplication. This space can be interpreted as the space of functions on the cyclic group of order formula_22, formula_1, or equivalently as the group ring of formula_1.
* Circulant matrices form a commutative algebra, since for any two given circulant matrices formula_40 and formula_41, the sum formula_42 is circulant, the product formula_43 is circulant, and formula_44.
* For a nonsingular circulant matrix formula_40, its inverse formula_46 is also circulant. For a singular circulant matrix, its Moore–Penrose pseudoinverse formula_47 is circulant.
* The discrete Fourier transform matrix of order formula_22 is defined as by
